    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3809092520" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3809092520" />
    <a title="Kate" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/86104243-kate"><img alt="Kate" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602982838p2/86104243.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3809092520?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kate" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kate" href="/user/show/86104243-kate">Kate</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781400096985" href="/book/show/92936.Red_Azalea">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/86104243-kate?shelf=multicultural">multicultural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/86104243-kate?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/86104243-kate?shelf=buzzwordathon-2021">buzzwordathon-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/86104243-kate?shelf=lgbtq">lgbtq</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/86104243-kate?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3809092520" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17145285393720549948">This book was amazing! Anchee Min tells her story of growing up during China&apos;s Cultural Revolution in spare but beautiful prose. She begins in childhood, where she was forced to denounce a beloved teacher to win favour with the Communists. She then spends the bulk of the story exploring her life on a work farm where she engaged in an illicit sexual relationship with another woman. Finally, she writes about her experience being cast and starring in a Maoist propaganda film and the destiny of Chin</span>
  <span id="freeText17145285393720549948" style="display:none">This book was amazing! Anchee Min tells her story of growing up during China's Cultural Revolution in spare but beautiful prose. She begins in childhood, where she was forced to denounce a beloved teacher to win favour with the Communists. She then spends the bulk of the story exploring her life on a work farm where she engaged in an illicit sexual relationship with another woman. Finally, she writes about her experience being cast and starring in a Maoist propaganda film and the destiny of China following Mao's death. I have read some Cultural Revolution memoirs before, and really enjoyed them all. However, I feel that this one was unique and particularly powerful. At first, I found the writing a bit choppy, but eventually this became so effective that I felt I was living through Anchee's life right along with her. It's amazing that she was able to write so well in her second language. I definitely want to get into Anchee Min's fiction soon, and I am sure this book will stick with me for quite awhile. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17145285393720549948" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

