        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer324251423" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7155693196549793149">Min writes an honest memoir of coming-of-age through Mao&apos;s cultural revolution. I was going to write bluntly honest, but decided that blunt described the memoir itself. Her sentence structure is short and punchy. She tells it as it was. She bares her emotions, rubbed raw by injustice and oppression. Nearly everyone is broken by Mao&apos;s machine.<br/> <br/>I found her stories of farm labor interesting. Her relationship with Yan surprised me - in its innocence and path. Found it hard to believe that they could</span>
  <span id="freeText7155693196549793149" style="display:none">Min writes an honest memoir of coming-of-age through Mao's cultural revolution. I was going to write bluntly honest, but decided that blunt described the memoir itself. Her sentence structure is short and punchy. She tells it as it was. She bares her emotions, rubbed raw by injustice and oppression. Nearly everyone is broken by Mao's machine.<br /> <br />I found her stories of farm labor interesting. Her relationship with Yan surprised me - in its innocence and path. Found it hard to believe that they could share a bed and not be found out. But this was a memoir, and it was true. <br /><br />The summary of how she ended up in the states was also blunt. I would have liked more info on it, a follow-up book perhaps?</span>
  <a data-text-id="7155693196549793149" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

